      <section eId="sec_CCRP-229">
        <num>CCRP 229</num>
        <heading>229. Â Duties of officer in charge</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-229__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Of the charge against him;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-229__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Of his rights to communicate with and procure counsel; and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-229__subsec_3">
          <num>(3)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Of his right to request a preliminary examination when he is charged with a felony.
The officer in charge shall, within forty-eight hours from the time of the booking, notify the district attorney in writing of all persons booked for violation of state statutes, and shall furnish without cost a certified copy of any booking entry to any person requesting it.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112385</p>
